parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, hesitate, or jerk while accelerating, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

the vehicle loses motive power
the vehicle decelerates to a low speed
the vehicle fails to shift into gear
the transmission slips or shakes

the vehicle runs rough

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front passenger airbag can cause bodily harm, injury, or death to the passenger in the event of a collision.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
